.TH WS-CAMERAD 8 "February 2026" "ws-camerad 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
ws-camerad \- high-performance multi-consumer camera daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ws-camerad
.RB [ \-c
.IR config-file ]
.RB [ \-d ]
.RB [ \-h ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ws-camerad
is a high-performance camera daemon designed for Raspberry Pi with libcamera.
It provides continuous H.264 hardware encoding, RTSP streaming, shared memory
frame distribution, still image capture, and video clip extraction.
.PP
The daemon supports multiple simultaneous consumers through shared memory
(for raw YUV420 and BGR frames) and RTSP streaming (for H.264 video).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " config-file"
Use the specified configuration file instead of the default
.IR /etc/ws/camerad/ws-camerad.conf .
.TP
.B \-d
Run in debug mode with verbose logging.
.TP
.B \-h
Display help message and exit.
.SH CONTROL INTERFACE
The daemon listens on a Unix domain socket (default:
.IR /run/ws-camerad/control.sock )
for control commands.
.PP
Supported commands:
.TP
.B GET STATUS
Returns JSON status with frame counts, FPS, buffer usage, etc.
.TP
.B STILL
Capture a JPEG still image.
.TP
.BI "CLIP " seconds
Extract a video clip of the specified duration from the ring buffer.
.TP
.BI "SET " "parameter value"
Set a camera control parameter (e.g., SET brightness 0.2).
.SH CAMERA CONTROLS
Supported camera controls:
.TP
.B brightness
Range: -1.0 to 1.0 (0.0 = normal)
.TP
.B contrast
Range: 0.0 to 32.0 (1.0 = normal)
.TP
.B saturation
Range: 0.0 to 32.0 (1.0 = normal)
.TP
.B sharpness
Range: 0.0 to 16.0 (1.0 = normal)
.TP
.B ae_enable
Boolean: 0 = manual exposure, 1 = auto exposure
.TP
.B awb_enable
Boolean: 0 = manual white balance, 1 = auto white balance
.TP
.B exposure_time
Exposure time in microseconds (when ae_enable = 0)
.TP
.B gain
Analogue gain value (when ae_enable = 0)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ws/camerad/ws-camerad.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I /run/ws-camerad/control.sock
Control socket for client communication.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ws-camerad/stills/
Directory for captured still images.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ws-camerad/clips/
Directory for extracted video clips.
.SH SHARED MEMORY
The daemon creates POSIX shared memory segments for frame distribution:
.TP
.I /ws_camerad_frames
Raw YUV420 frames from libcamera.
.TP
.I /ws_camerad_frames_bgr
BGR24 frames converted for OpenCV consumers.
.SH RTSP STREAMING
When RTSP is enabled, the daemon streams H.264 video at:
.PP
.RS
rtsp://\fIhostname\fP:8554/camera
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B ws-camerad
returns 0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with default configuration:
.PP
.RS
.B ws-camerad
.RE
.PP
Start with custom configuration:
.PP
.RS
.B ws-camerad -c /path/to/config.conf
.RE
.PP
Capture a still image via Python:
.PP
.RS
from ws_camerad import CameraClient
.br
c = CameraClient()
.br
c.capture_still()
.RE
